divs: Sighting DetailsWent out to smoke about an hour ago and noticed star like object in sky slightly above eastern horizon and noticed it was brighter than other stars. Went back out an hour later and it has dramatically moved much high than before. Looked at object through binoculars and it is a very bright star looking type object that is much closer than a star but hard to make out with binoculars. It is still in eastern sky as I am reporting this. Would not be reporting if I didn't find it an interesting object that is not usually in the sky.
Summary: Noticed star like object in eastern sky around 11pm and it's moving slowly north faster than other stars
